# Task 1: Create a script to generate 5-smooth numbers, whose prime divisors are less or equal to 5. They are also called Hamming/Regular/Ugly numbers.
X ← /× ˜ⁿ[2 3 5]
⟜X ⌈×10 ⍥⚂3

# Task 2: Create a script that generates Pascal Triangle. Accept number of rows from the command line. The Pascal Triangle should have at least 3 rows.
Pascal ← ≡&p ⍥(⊙□+⊸⊃˜⊂⊂ 0)⊙[1]
Pascal 9
